Project Information:
- Title: Autonomous AI Agents for Spacecraft Operations
- Description: This research proposal focuses on developing autonomous AI agents for spacecraft operations, specifically in Guidance, Navigation, and Control (GNC) and Attitude and Orbit Control Systems (AOCS), as well as remote sensing. The vision is to create AI-driven agents capable of real-time communication with spacecraft systems and autonomously managing and controlling spacecraft functions. The objectives include reducing human involvement in mission-critical tasks, minimizing human error, and enhancing overall mission efficiency and safety. The proposal outlines expected technical innovations, such as advanced AI algorithms for decision-making under uncertainty and reliable system integration. Challenges to address include ensuring AI reliability and effective decision-making in uncertain environments. The potential impacts on the space exploration industry include increased mission efficiency, safety, and reduced operational costs.
- Abstract: The Autonomous AI Agents for Spacecraft Operations project aims to revolutionize spacecraft operations by integrating advanced AI technologies into guidance, navigation, and control (GNC) systems, as well as attitude and orbit control systems (AOCS). These AI agents are designed to enhance autonomy, enabling spacecraft to make real-time decisions, adapt to unforeseen circumstances, and optimize mission objectives with minimal human intervention. Key innovations include high-integrity algorithms for autonomous mission planning, intelligent docking, and multi-agent coordination, which collectively improve decision-making under uncertainty. The project addresses the challenges of limited real-time communication with Earth by employing AI-driven systems for data processing and pattern recognition, thus enhancing mission efficiency and safety. The integration process follows a structured systems engineering approach, ensuring seamless operation across all mission segments. Despite potential risks such as environmental challenges and ethical considerations, the project emphasizes reliability through explainability and certification of AI systems. By reducing human involvement in mission-critical tasks, the project anticipates significant cost reductions and increased scientific returns, paving the way for more complex and ambitious space exploration missions.

